    {3972,"Disrupting Shadows",136201,2,0,2,{"wago"},"Warlord Zon'ozz covers random players with Disrupting Shadows. The effect inflicts $%103434s1 Shadow damage every $103434t1 seconds. The shadows also deal $103948s2 Shadow damage and knockback the targeted player if the effect is dispelled.$[5,6\n\n\n\nIn Heroic Difficulty the effect deals $103948s2 Shadow damage and knocks back all players within $103948A1 yards.$]",15,0,0,128,324,4364,3,0,0},
    {3973,"Void of the Unmaking",463569,0,0,1,{"wago"},"Warlord Zon'ozz summons a Void of the Unmaking. This void travels forward until it encounters a soul to absorb.",-1,4322,0,32,324,0,5,0,0},
    {3974,"Void Bolt",237561,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Yor'sahj the Unsleeping blasts his primary target with dark energy, dealing $%104849s1 Shadow damage initially and then $%104849s2 Shadow damage every $104849t2 seconds. This effect stacks.",-1,0,0,0,325,3978,1,0,0},
    {3978,"Call Blood of Shu'ma",136016,2,0,1,{"wago"},"Yor'sahj the Unsleeping calls to the might of Shu'ma, summoning three differently colored globules of his blood. These globules path slowly towards Yor'sahj, infusing him with additional powers if they reach him.$[5,6\n\n\n\nIn Heroic difficulty four slimes answer Yor'sahj's call.$]",-1,3979,0,32,325,0,2,0,0},
    {3979,"Fusing Vapors",236271,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The blood globules emit a fusing vapor when damaged below 50% health that heals all other active globules for $103635s1% of their maximum life.\n\n\n\nWhen one globule dies, the surviving globules completely fuse and gain immunity to all forms of damage.",-1,0,0,0,325,3980,3,3978,0},
    {3980,"Glowing Globule",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"When a Glowing Globule reaches Yor'sahj, it infuses Yor'sahj with the Glowing Blood of Shu'ma.",-1,4317,39249,0,325,3981,4,3978,0},
    {3981,"Cobalt Globule",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"When a Cobalt Globule reaches Yor'sahj, it infuses Yor'sahj with the ability to summon Mana Voids.",-1,4318,39251,0,325,3982,6,3978,0},
    {3982,"Crimson Globule",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"When a Crimson Globule reaches Yor'sahj, it infuses Yor'sahj with the Searing Blood ability.",-1,4319,39628,0,325,3983,9,3978,0},
    {3983,"Dark Globule",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"When a Dark Globule reaches Yor'sahj, the corruption of the blood seeps out into the Maw of Shu'ma. This vile corruption then periodically creates Forgotten Ones that attack the players.",-1,3984,39252,0,325,3986,11,3978,0},
    {3984,"Forgotten One",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"These creatures fixate on a random target.",-1,3985,27849,0,325,0,12,3983,0},
    {3985,"Psychic Slice",132303,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Forgotten One emits a wave of psychic force at its current target, inflicting $%105671s1 Shadow damage.",-1,0,0,0,325,0,13,3984,0},
    {3986,"Acidic Globule",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"When an Acidic Globule reaches Yor'sahj, the Maw of Shu'ma infuses with the acidic blood and stimulates further Digestive Acid production.",-1,4320,36110,0,325,3987,14,3978,0},
    {3987,"Shadowed Globule",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"When a Shadowed Globule reaches Yor'sahj, it infuses Yor'sahj with the Deep Corruption ability.",-1,4321,39248,0,325,0,17,3978,0},
    {3988,"Zon'ozz Diffused",0,0,0,0,{"wago"},"When the Void collides with Warlord Zon'ozz, it inflicts a distracting shock to him. The Void Diffusion increases the damage Zon'ozz takes by $104031s1% for every time the Void of the Unmaking bounces between players. This collision enrages Warlord Zon'ozz, causing him to awaken the Maw of Go'rath and lose his Focused Anger.$[5,6\n\n\n\nIn Heroic Difficulty the awakening of the Maw of Go'rath causes many different types of tentacles to emerge and attack the players.$]",-1,4267,0,32,324,0,9,3973,0},
    {3989,"Claw of Go'rath",0,1,0,2,{"wago"},nil,12,4263,39132,1,324,3990,11,3988,0},
    {3990,"Eye of Go'rath",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,4265,28615,0,324,4266,13,3988,0},
    {4027,"Stage One: Dragonriders, Attack!",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},"Flying alongside the Skyfire and surveying the scene while his massive twilight drake lobs balls of destruction at the gunship, Warmaster Blackhorn gives the order for his elite dragonriders to swoop into battle.",-1,4202,0,0,332,4033,1,0,0},
    {4033,"Stage Two: Looks Like I'm Doing This Myself",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},"Once the Skyfire's defenders defeat three waves of dragonriders, Warmaster Blackhorn leaps down onto the deck of the gunship.",-1,4034,0,0,332,0,18,0,0},
    {4034,"Warmaster Blackhorn",236299,1,0,1,{"wago"},nil,-1,4209,39399,0,332,4206,19,4033,0},
    {4037,"Assault Aspect",575534,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Deathwing searches for his next enemy to assault.  Deathwing assaults the platform with the largest number of players and an attached limb.",-1,0,0,32,333,4102,2,4040,0},
    {4038,"Limb Tentacle",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"Deathwing grasps onto each platform with one of his limbs.",-1,4039,39354,0,333,4112,13,4040,0},
    {4039,"Burning Blood",237513,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Burning Blood gushes from the Tentacle, inflicting Fire damage every $105401t1 sec. The damage increases as the Limb Tentacle's health lowers.",-1,0,0,0,333,4103,14,4038,0},
    {4040,"Stage One: The Final Assault",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},"Deathwing assaults his enemies while attached to the platforms by his twisted limbs.",-1,4037,0,0,333,4046,1,0,0},
    {4046,"Stage Two: The Last Stand",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},"At 20% remaining health, Deathwing falls forward onto the platform.",-1,4350,0,0,333,4123,21,0,0},
    {4050,"Roll",236372,2,0,1,{"wago"},"Throughout the encounter, Deathwing tries to throw players from his back when he senses that they are all standing on the same side of his spine. During a roll, Deathwing throws off all players and other creatures not attached to his back.",-1,0,0,48,318,3923,1,0,0},
    {4051,"Burning Tendons",0,0,0,0,{"wago"},"Players expose Burning Tendons when they pry up one of Deathwing's armor plates. Destroying these fibrous strands is the key to removing an armor plate.",-1,4052,0,2,318,0,3,3923,0},
    {4052,"Seal Armor Breach",538043,2,0,0,{"wago"},"After the players pry up an armor plate, the Burning Tendons rapidly pull the plate closed, protecting the tendons from further damage and preventing the plate from flying off.",-1,0,0,0,318,0,4,4051,0},
    {4053,"Fiery Grip",538041,2,0,2,{"wago"},"The Corrupton grips victims with a whip-like cord of plasma, stunning them for up to $105490d. and inflicting $%105490s2 Fire damage every $105490t2 sec. The corruption must channel to maintain this effect, and players may break the channel by inflicting significant damage to the tentacle. This effect prevents players from being thrown off Deathwing's back.",15,0,0,0,318,0,9,3920,0},
    {4054,"Hideous Amalgamation",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"These unstable creatures are a patchwork of Elementium Armor fragments and pieces of the former Dragon's body held together by his molten blood.",-1,4058,38549,33,318,4055,10,3929,0},
    {4055,"Corrupted Blood",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"These living globs of Deathwing's blood appear fragile, but leave behind an indestructible residue when killed.",-1,4056,38548,1,318,0,19,3929,0},
    {4056,"Burst",459026,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Corrupted Blood explodes when destroyed, inflicting $%105219s1 Physical damage to nearby enemies within $105219A1 yards.",-1,0,0,0,318,4057,20,4055,0},
    {4057,"Residue",135805,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Destroying a Corrupted Blood leaves behind an indestructible residue. It slowly creeps toward the nearest hole in Deathwing's Back where it reconstitutes into a new Corrupted Blood.",-1,0,0,0,318,0,21,4055,0},
    {4058,"Absorb Blood",463567,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Amalgamation absorbs nearby Corrupted Blood residue. The Amalgamation grows more unstable with each Residue absorbed, increasing its damage by $105248s1% and attack speed by $105248s2%. At $105248U stacks it becomes superheated.",-1,0,0,0,318,4059,11,4054,0},
    {4059,"Superheated Nucleus",132847,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The core of the Amalgamation becomes critically unstable, causing it to inflict $%106264s1 Fire damage to all enemies every $105834t1 sec. If the players destroy the Amalgamation in this state, then it will trigger a Nuclear Blast.",-1,0,0,0,318,4060,12,4054,0},
    {4060,"Nuclear Blast",133035,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The superheated nucleus of the Amalgamation triggers a massive explosion, inflicting $%105845s1 Fire damage to targets within $105845A1 yds. This powerful blast pries up one of Deathwing's Elementium plates if it is within range.",-1,0,0,48,318,4061,13,4054,0},
    {4061,"Degradation",236290,2,0,2,{"wago"},"Destroyed Amalgamations degrade the maximum health of all enemy targets by $106005s1%. This effect occurs regardless of the state of the nucleus and stacks up to $106005u times.",12,0,0,12,318,4062,14,4054,0},
    {4062,"Blood Corruption: Death",538040,2,0,2,{"wago"},"Deathwing's corruption courses through your veins. This corruption takes hold if it is not removed quickly, infecting the player with the Blood of Deathwing. When dispelled this effect jumps to a new target and can mutate into Blood Corruption: Earth.",12,4063,0,140,318,4064,15,4054,0},
    {4063,"Blood of Deathwing",538040,2,0,2,{"wago"},"The blood of Deathwing explodes violently from your veins, inflicting $%106201s1 Fire damage to you and several other players.",12,0,0,24,318,0,16,4062,0},
    {4064,"Blood Corruption: Earth",132842,2,0,2,{"wago"},"A shadow of Neltharion courses through your veins. This corruption takes hold if it is not removed quickly, infecting the player with the Blood of Neltharion. When dispelled this effect jumps to a new target and can mutate into Blood Corruption: Death.",12,4065,0,140,318,0,17,4054,0},
    {4065,"Blood of Neltharion",132842,2,0,2,{"wago"},"The barest hint of a shadow of the former Earth-Warder suffuses your blood. Damage taken from all sources is reduced by $106213s1%. This effect can stack up to $106213U times.",12,0,0,8,318,0,18,4064,0},
    {4069,"Binding Crystal",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"Destroying all four of the binding crystals stops Hagara's channeling of Frozen Tempest.",-1,0,26620,0,317,3915,6,3914,0},
    {4070,"Bound Lightning Elementals",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"Hagara calls elementals to aid her during the Lightning Storm. When a player kills an elemental,  it causes a nearby Crystal Conductor to overload and electrocute nearby players.",-1,0,34548,0,317,4328,14,3918,0},
    {4072,"Wither Will",237563,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Sha of Doubt withers the will of 2 random players, inflicting $106736s1 Shadow damage.",-1,0,0,0,335,5724,1,0,0},
    {4076,"Figments of Doubt",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"The Sha of Doubt forces all players to face a figment of their own doubt.",-1,5725,40625,32,335,0,3,0,0},
    {4091,"Drain Essence",136169,2,0,2,{"wago"},"At 60% remaining health, Peroth'arn stuns all enemies and inflicts Shadow damage every second for $104905d.",-2,0,0,0,290,4092,5,0,0},
    {4092,"The Eyes of Peroth'arn",0,0,0,3,{"wago"},"After Illidan interrupts Drain Essence, Peroth'arn returns to the shadows to ambush the heroes. Peroth'arn unleashes his Eyes of Peroth'arn to search for the players. Players gain the protection of their Shadowcloaks to help them avoid the detection range of the Eyes.\n\n\n\nIf players avoid detection for 40 seconds, Peroth'arn becomes visible and weakened with the Enfeebled effect.\n\n\n\nIf an Eye of Peroth'arn discovers a player, Peroth'arn marks the player with Easy Prey, leaps out of the shadows, and attacks the discovered player.",-2,4225,0,32,290,4100,6,0,0},
    {4100,"Endless Frenzy",132344,2,0,2,{"wago"},"At 20% remaining health, Peroth'arn frenzies and increases his damage by $105521s1%.",-2,0,0,0,290,0,10,0,0},
    {4102,"Cataclysm",575535,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Deathwing attempts to finish the job he started by bringing forth a second Cataclysm, inflicting $%106523s1 Fire damage to all players.",-1,0,0,16,333,4106,3,4040,0},
    {4103,"Blistering Tentacle",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"At 75%, 50%, and 25% remaining health the Limb Tentacle sprouts several Blistering Tentacles that are immune to Area of Effect abilities.",-1,4104,39347,0,333,4105,15,4038,0},
    {4104,"Blistering Heat",236305,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Blistering Heat inflicts $%105445s1 Fire damage every $105444t1 sec, and increases its damage by $105445s2% for $105445d. This effect stacks.",-1,0,0,0,333,0,16,4103,0},
    {4105,"Agonizing Pain",135860,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The pain from severing Deathwing's limb interrupts his concentration, stunning him and inflicting $106548s1% of his health in damage.",-1,0,0,0,333,0,17,4038,0},
    {4106,"Elementium Bolt",135821,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Deathwing creates an Elementium Bolt, sending it to the target platform.",-1,4107,0,0,333,4347,4,4040,0},
    {4107,"Elementium Blast",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"If the Elementium Bolt reaches its destination, the bolt inflicts $%105723s1 Fire damage to all players and an additional $105723s2 Fire damage every $105723t2 sec until players destroy the Elementium Bolt. The initial damage decreases the further the player stands from the targeted location.",-1,0,39381,0,333,0,5,4106,0},
    {4108,"Hemorrhage",135822,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Deathwing's tentacle begins to Hemorrhage, creating several Regenerative Blood at a nearby location.",-1,4109,0,0,333,4038,9,4040,0},
    {4109,"Regenerative Blood",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"The Regenerative Blood of Deathwing forms. Regenerative Bloods gain ten energy every $105932t1 sec.  The melee attacks of a Regenerative Blood also cause Degenerative Bite.",-1,4110,38548,0,333,0,10,4108,0},
    {4110,"Regenerative",237536,2,0,0,{"wago"},"A Regenerative Blood heals to full health when it reaches maximum energy.$[7\n\n\n\nIn Raid Finder Difficulty, Regenerative Blood heals 50% of max health when it reaches maximum energy.$]",-1,0,0,0,333,4111,11,4109,0},
    {4111,"Degenerative Bite",237514,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Melee attacks cause Degenerative Bite, inflicting $%105841s1 Shadow damage every $105841t1 sec for $105841d. This effect stacks.",-1,0,0,0,333,0,12,4109,0},
    {4112,"Mutated Corruption",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"A Mutated Corruption appears shortly after assaulting a platform.",-1,4113,39405,0,333,0,18,4040,0},
    {4113,"Crush",236316,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The crushing weight of the Mutated Corruption inflicts $%106385s1 Physical damage to enemies in a cone in front of the Corruption.",-1,0,0,0,333,4114,19,4112,0},
    {4114,"Impale",132312,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Mutated Corruption impales its target, inflicting $%106444s1 Physical damage to the target.",-1,0,0,17,333,0,20,4112,0},
    {4115,"Elementium Fragment",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"Pieces of Deathwing's armor chip off, forming three Elementium Fragments nearby.$[4,6,7\n\n\n\nIn 25 player raids, eight Elementium Fragments form.$]",-1,4116,39347,0,333,4117,24,4046,0},
