    {6244,"Amber Scalpel",135279,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Un'sok carves the ground with a focused beam of pure amber energy. The beam inflicts $121995s1 Nature damage every $121994t1 sec. at the point of contact, and leaves behind Molten Amber residue. The residue inflicts $122005s1 Fire damage every $122004t1 sec. to players who touch it. Some of this residue congeals into Living Amber oozes.",-1,6261,0,0,737,6245,2,6243,0},
    {6245,"Parasitic Growth",576313,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Amber-Shaper Un'sok causes amber to grow within the body of a random target, inflicting $121949s1 Nature damage every $121949t1 sec. This strain of amber absorbs healing energy, increasing the damage it inflicts to its host in direct proportion to any healing received. After $121949d, the unstable parasite dissipates without a trace.",-1,0,0,4,737,6248,5,6243,0},
    {6246,"Stage Two: Un'sok's Greatest Creation",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},"When Un'sok reaches 70% remaining health, he calls forth a massive Amber Monstrosity to fight beside him. Un'sok continues to attack with his full arsenal of abilities from Stage One.",-1,6254,0,0,737,6247,15,0,0},
    {6247,"Stage Three: Un'sok Unleashed",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},"Upon witnessing the destruction of his greatest creation, Un'sok channels power from the amber pools lining his chamber and prepares to make his final stand. Un'sok no longer uses Amber Scalpel, but now casts Reshape Life with greatly increased frequency.",-1,6258,0,0,737,0,22,0,0},
    {6248,"Reshape Life",463485,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Un'sok unleashes a torrent of amber at a player, transforming the target into a misshapen mass of flowing amber that is hostile to players and monsters alike.",-1,6249,0,0,737,6658,6,6243,0},
    {6249,"Mutated Construct",0,1,0,1,{"wago"},"While transformed, the player continuously expends Willpower to retain control over the twisted form, at the rate of 2 per second, beginning with a maximum of 100. When Willpower runs out, the player dies and the Mutated Construct continues to act, uncontrolled.",-1,6263,42890,0,737,0,7,6248,0},
    {6250,"Amber Strike",132109,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The construct inflicts $122389s1 Nature damage to the current hostile target and interrupts normal spellcasting, including attempts by other constructs, or by the Amber Monstrosity, to trigger an Amber Explosion. Amber Strike also destabilizes the target, increasing damage taken by $123059s1% for $123059d. This effect stacks.",-1,0,0,0,737,6251,9,6249,0},
    {6251,"Break Free",135791,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Once the physical form of the amber construct has been reduced to 20% of its maximum health, the player can break free with a great surge of will. The player then regains their natural form.$[7\n\n\n\nIn Raid Finder Difficulty, this ability will activate automatically if a transformed construct is damaged below 10% of its maximum health.$]",-1,0,0,32,737,6259,10,6249,0},
    {6252,"Struggle for Control",136035,2,0,0,{"wago"},"With a surge of will, the player expends 8 Willpower to force the mutated form to cease all action for $122395d. This also increases the mutated form's damage taken by $124802s1% for $124802d.",-1,0,0,32,737,6253,12,6249,0},
    {6253,"Smash",132109,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Transformed players use this simple melee attack in lieu of their normal attack, inflicting $122960s1 Physical damage to a target.",-1,0,0,0,737,0,13,6249,0},
    {6254,"Amber Monstrosity",0,0,0,0,{"wago"},"Un'sok formed this towering behemoth entirely of flowing amber, and it stands as a triumph of Un'sok's research into creating life from the mantids' amber.",-1,6255,0,0,737,6264,16,6246,0},
    {6255,"Amber Explosion",236305,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Monstrosity releases a massive explosion of amber energy, inflicting $122402s1 Nature damage to all players.",-1,0,0,0,737,6256,17,6254,0},
    {6256,"Massive Stomp",132847,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Monstrosity stomps the ground forcefully, inflicting $122408s1 Physical damage to all enemies within $122408A1 yards and knocking them back.",-1,0,0,0,737,6257,18,6254,0},
    {6257,"Fling",463444,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Monstrosity grabs its current target in one of its massive hands and hurls the hapless victim at a distant player, causing $122457s1 Physical damage to targets within $122457A1 yards of the point of impact and stunning them for $122457d.",-1,0,0,1,737,6659,19,6254,0},
    {6258,"Concentrated Mutation",236305,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Un'sok draws massive amounts of amber energy into his body, increasing his damage dealt by $122556s1% and attack speed by $122556s2%.",-1,0,0,0,737,6260,23,6247,0},
    {6259,"Consume Amber",576313,2,0,0,{"wago"},"A transformed player consumes a pool of Burning Amber left behind by a defeated Living Amber. The consumption restores $123156s2 Willpower, but also bolsters the mutated form, increasing its current and maximum health by $122516s1.$[5,6 \n\n\n\nIn Heroic difficulty, Consume Amber restores 50 Willpower when used during Stage Three of the encounter.$]",-1,0,0,0,737,6252,11,6249,0},
    {6260,"Volatile Amber",525023,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Un'sok's siphoning agitates the pools of amber around the room, causing them to periodically emit bursts of amber that fly through the air at high velocity. Each amber burst inflicts $123014s1 Nature damage to any player it strikes. If a missile strikes a player while they are transformed into a Mutated Construct, it heals them for $123198s1% of their health.",-1,0,0,0,737,6548,24,6247,0},
    {6261,"Living Amber",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"Each of these animated amber oozes focuses mindlessly on a random player, emanating a Corrosive Aura that inflicts $122349s1 Nature damage every $122348t1 sec to all players. Each ooze Bursts in a shower of amber when destroyed, inficting $122532s1 Nature damage to enemies within $122532A1 yards and healing any other Living Amber within that radius for $122532s2% of their maximum health.$[5,6 \n\n\n\nIn Heroic difficulty, dissolved Living Amber will reconstitute after 30 seconds.$]$[7\n\n\n\nIn Looking for Raid difficulty, destroying a Living Amber does not heal other nearby Living Amber.$]",-1,6567,33921,0,737,0,3,6244,0},
    {6262,"Bloody Mess",236268,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Houndmaster Braun's knife attacks inflict $114056s1 damage to an enemy every $114056t sec. for $114056d. This effect stacks.\n\n\n\nBraun applies this effect to any target hit by Piercing Throw or Death Blossom.",-1,0,0,0,660,5608,3,0,0},
    {6263,"Amber Explosion",236305,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The amber encircling the mutated player compels the unleashing of a massive explosion, inflicting $122398s1 Nature damage to all players.",-1,0,0,16,737,6250,8,6249,0},
    {6264,"Amber Carapace",132847,2,0,0,{"wago"},"While the Amber Monstrosity lives, an Amber Carapace shields Amber-Shaper Un'sok. The Carapace reduces his damage taken by $122540s1%.",-1,0,0,0,737,0,21,6246,0},
    {6265,"Fury",132141,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Fury increases Garalon's damage dealt by $122754s1% and movement speed by $122754s3% for $122754d. This effect stacks.",-1,0,0,1,713,0,2,6122,0},
    {6266,"Crush",451165,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Garalon crushes his foes, inflicting $122774s3 Physical damage to all players. Any player within $122774A2 yards receives an additional $122774s2 Physical damage as Garalon's body slams down upon them. Garalon's massive bulk also knocks down all players for $122774d. Garalon crushes foes whenever he detects their presence beneath him.$[3,4\n\n\n\nIn Normal Difficulty, Garalon also crushes foes when Pheromones passes to a new target.$]$[5,6\n\n\n\nIn Heroic Difficulty, Garalon periodically crushes foes.$]",-1,0,0,16,713,6267,3,0,0},
    {6267,"Pheromones",136044,2,0,1,{"wago"},"Garalon surrounds a player with powerful pheromones, fixating on the target.  \n\n\n\nEvery $122835t1 sec. the Pheromones inflict $123092s2 Nature damage to all players and Pungency on the target, then spawn a Pheromone Trail.\n\n\n\nPheromones pass to allies in close proximity.",-1,6268,0,32,713,6270,4,0,0},
    {6268,"Pungency",575589,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Exposure to Garalon's Pheromones renders the player extra pungent, increasing Pheromone damage by $123081s1% for $123081d. This effect stacks.",-1,0,0,0,713,6269,5,6267,0},
    {6269,"Pheromone Trail",136044,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Pheromone Trail on the ground inflicts $123120s1 Nature damage to players within $123120A1 yards.",-1,0,0,0,713,0,6,6267,0},
    {6270,"Garalon's Legs",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},"Players attack Garalon's legs separately from his body.",-1,6271,0,2,713,6294,7,0,0},
    {6271,"Weak Point",132295,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Close proximity to Garalon's leg allows attackers to see weak points, increasing their damage dealt to the leg by $123423s1%.",-1,0,0,0,713,6272,8,6270,0},
    {6272,"Broken Leg",460686,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Breaking one of Garalon's legs damages Garalon for $122786s3% of his maximum health and reduces Garalon's movement speed by $122786s1%.  This effect stacks up to $122786U times.",-1,0,0,0,713,6273,9,6270,0},
    {6273,"Mend Leg",136043,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Garalon periodically mends one of his broken legs, restoring it to full health.",-1,0,0,0,713,0,10,6270,0},
    {6274,"The Escaped Prisoners",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},"The mantid captured these three Pandaren during the initial attack on Niuzao Temple, but the prisoners were able to break free of their bindings and fight back. Now they stand ready to do whatever it takes to end the siege.",-1,6278,0,0,738,6279,1,0,0},
    {6278,"Caustic Tar",134438,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Escaped prisoners, Li and Lo Chu, will position and prepare mantid tar kegs for use in the battle.\n\n\n\nPlayers can throw the kegs of Caustic Tar onto the battlefield. Caustic Tar inflicts on any unit standing within the tar $120269m1 Nature damage, reduces movement speed by 50%, and increases damage taken by $120778m1%. This effect stacks.\n\n\n\nThe Caustic Tar also removes any effect from the target that increases movement or attack speed.",-1,0,0,160,738,0,2,6274,0},
    {6279,"Stage One: Bring It!",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},"Commander Vo'jak orders his forces to attack the players.",-1,6280,0,0,738,6284,3,0,0},
    {6280,"Sik'thik Swarmer",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"Lightly armored and well trained, the Sik'thik Swarmers are a key part of the Vo'jak's forces.",-1,0,42193,0,738,6281,4,6279,0},
    {6281,"Sik'thik Amberwing",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"The Sik'thik Amberwing flies to the top of the platform and bombards the players.",-1,6289,43955,0,738,6282,5,6279,0},
    {6282,"Sik'thik Demolisher",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"Quick and volatile, these mantid carry explosive charges.",-1,6290,42875,0,738,6283,7,6279,0},
    {6283,"Sik'thik Warrior",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"Sik'thik Warriors slowly advance on the enemy position.",-1,0,42207,0,738,0,9,6279,0},
    {6284,"Stage Two: Your Defenses Did Not Stop Me!",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},"Commander Vo'jak's enters the battle as his forces near defeat at the hands of the players.",-1,6285,0,0,738,0,10,0,0},
    {6285,"Rising Speed",460953,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Commander Vo'jak focuses his will and determination, increasing his attack speed by $120758s1% every $120757t sec. This effect stacks.",-1,0,0,0,738,6286,11,6284,0},
    {6286,"Dashing Strike",132337,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Commander Vo'jak charges a random enemy player, inflicting $120807m1 Physical damage to all enemies passed through. The Strike also knocks back his current target, inflicting an additional $120800m2 Physical damage.",-1,0,0,0,738,6287,12,6284,0},
    {6287,"Thousand Blades",132369,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Immediately after using Dashing Strike, Commander Vo'jak begins to spin around and send blades outward, inflicting Physical damage to all targets within $120760A1 yards.\n\n\n\nThousand Blades also removes the Caustic Tar effect.",-1,0,0,0,738,0,13,6284,0},
    {6289,"Bombard",459027,2,0,1,{"wago"},"The Sik'thik Amberwing fires a volley of explosives at random enemy locations every $120559t1 sec. for $120559d. Bombard inflicts $120200s1 Fire damage to all creatures within $120200A1 yards of the targeted location.",-1,0,0,32,738,0,6,6281,0},
    {6290,"Unstable Blast",136173,2,0,1,{"wago"},"The Sik'thik Demolisher carries unstable explosives and explodes when damaged or killed, inflicting $121981m1 to all targets within $121981A1 yards.",-1,0,0,32,738,0,8,6282,0},
    {6294,"Damaged",538768,2,0,2,{"wago"},"In Heroic difficulty, Garalon gains the Damaged effect upon reaching 33% remaining health.",12,6295,0,8,713,0,11,0,0},
    {6295,"Pheromones",136044,2,0,2,{"wago"},"While Garalon has the Damaged effect, Garalon ignores the fixate effects of Pheromones.",12,0,0,32,713,6296,12,6294,0},
    {6296,"Melee Attack",615303,2,0,2,{"wago"},"While Garalon has the Damaged effect, Garalon uses his normal melee attack and gains a dramatic speed increase.",12,0,0,1,713,0,13,6294,0},
    {6297,"Treacherous Winds",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},"Twice during the fight Nero'nok lifts off and flies to the other end of the bridge. Upon landing he periodically channels Gusting Winds until interrupted.",-1,6203,0,32,727,0,4,0,0},
    {6299,"The Swarm",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},"Wind Lord Mel'jarak fights alongside his most trusted warriors.",-1,6332,0,0,741,0,8,0,0},
    {6300,"Sra'thik Amber-Trapper",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,6301,43085,0,741,6305,11,6299,0},
    {6301,"Amber Prison",463563,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Sra'thik Amber-Trappers imprison a random player and their allies within $121874A1 yards in amber, stunning them until freed.\n\n\n\nPlayers can smash an Amber Prison and free the imprisoned allies inside by interacting with it. Residue afflicts players who destroy Amber Prisons.",-1,6302,0,0,741,6303,12,6300,0},
    {6302,"Residue",135732,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Residue prevents a player from destroying Amber Prisons for $122055d.",-1,0,0,0,741,0,13,6301,0},
    {6303,"Corrosive Resin",576313,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Sra'thik Amber-Trappers cover a player in 5 stacks of Corrosive Resin for $122064d, inflicting $122064s1 Nature damage every second per stack. Moving while afflicted by Corrosive Resin removes a stack of Corrosive Resin and creates a Corrosive Resin Pool at the player's location.",-1,6304,0,0,741,0,14,6300,0},
    {6304,"Corrosive Resin Pool",535291,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Corrosive Resin Pools inflict $122125s1 Nature damage every second to all players within the pool.",-1,0,0,0,741,0,15,6303,0},
    {6305,"Zar'thik Battle-Mender",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,6306,43086,0,741,6334,16,6299,0},
    {6306,"Mending",535593,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Zar'thik Battle-Menders mend their allies, healing a group of the swarm for $122147s1% of their maximum health.",-1,0,0,64,741,6307,17,6305,0},
    {6307,"Quickening",132845,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Zar'thik Battle-Menders quicken all of Mel'jarak's swarm, increasing all damage done and melee attack speed by $122149s1% for $122149d. This effect stacks.",-1,0,0,128,741,0,18,6305,0},
    {6310,"The Night",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},"Tsulong struggles at Night with the Sha's corrupting influence. Bringing Tsulong's remaining health to zero while at Night permanently destroys the Sha's influence over him. When he reaches 100 energy, he temporarily purges the Sha's influence and radiant sunlight turns Night into Day.",-1,6311,0,0,742,6315,1,0,0},
    {6311,"Dread Shadows",236295,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Dread Shadows created by the Sha within Tsulong inflict $122768s1 Shadow damage on all players and increases their Dread Shadows damage taken by $122768s2%. This effect stacks.",-1,0,0,32,742,6312,2,6310,0},
    {6312,"Nightmares",136214,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Sha within Tsulong projects Nightmares at the location of a random player. The Nightmares inflict $122777s1 Shadow damage and fear players within $122777A1 yards of the impact for $122777d.",-1,0,0,128,742,6313,3,6310,0},
    {6313,"Shadow Breath",236302,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Tsulong expels out Sha energy in a 30 degree cone in front of him, inflicting $122752s1 Shadow damage and increasing Shadow damage taken by $122752s2% for $122752d. This effect stacks.",-1,0,0,1,742,6314,4,6310,0},
    {6314,"Sunbeam",135981,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Tsulong's attempts to resist the Sha allow him to protect the players from Dread Shadows. Tsulong summons a Sunbeam onto the battlefield, and the Sunbeam grants immunity to Dread Shadows for players standing within the beam. The protected area of the Sunbeam shrinks over time as more players stand within it.",-1,0,0,32,742,6550,5,6310,0},
    {6315,"The Day",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},"During the Day, Tsulong gains the upper hand over the Sha corruption. Players may heal and aid Tsulong during the Day, and bringing him to full health while in the Day permanently destroys the Sha's influence over him. When he reaches 100 energy, the Sha corrupts his emotions and Night descends upon the Terrace.",-1,6316,0,0,742,0,7,0,0},
    {6316,"Embodied Terror",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"Embodied Terrors spawn as the Sha fights to control Tsulong. When players destroy an Embodied Terror, five Fright Spawns burst out.",-1,6317,42420,0,742,6318,8,6315,0},
    {6317,"Terrorize",236296,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Embodied Terror casts Terrorize on both a random player and on Tsulong. The terror inflicts $123018s1% of the player's current health as Shadow damage every $123011t1 sec for $123011d. Tsulong suffers $123012s1% of his total health as Shadow damage every $123012t1 sec. for $123012d.",-1,0,0,128,742,0,9,6316,0},
    {6318,"Fright Spawn",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"Five Fright Spawns appear when players destroy an Embodied Terror.",-1,6319,40625,0,742,6320,10,6315,0},
    {6319,"Fright",136183,2,0,0,{"wago"},"A Fright Spawn unleashes a wave of Fright, inflicting $123036s1 Shadow damage and fear on players within $123036A1 yards for $123036d.",-1,0,0,128,742,0,11,6318,0},
    {6320,"Unstable Sha",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"Unstable Sha appear around Tsulong and then move towards him, inflicting massive Shadow damage to Tsulong if they reach him.",-1,6321,41677,0,742,6323,12,6315,0},
    {6321,"Unstable Bolt",136181,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Unstable Sha unleashes shadowy energy at a random player, inflicting $122881s1 Shadow damage on the target. The Unstable Bolt also damages the Unstable Sha for $122907s1% of its maximum health.",-1,0,0,0,742,6322,13,6320,0},
    {6322,"Instability",607852,2,0,0,{"wago"},"If an Unstable Sha reaches Tsulong, it inflicts $123697s2 Shadow damage on Tsulong and disappears.",-1,0,0,0,742,0,14,6320,0},
    {6323,"Sun Breath",535045,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Tsulong breathes out solar energy in a 60-degree cone in front of him, inflicting $122855s1 Nature damage to Sha within $122855A1 yards and stunning them for $122855d. The breath also places the Bathed in Light effect on players within its area.",-1,6324,0,0,742,6551,15,6315,0},
    {6324,"Bathed in Light",535045,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The warmth of the Sun instantly restores $122858s2% of a player's total mana and increases their healing done by $122858s1% for $122858d.",-1,0,0,0,742,0,16,6323,0},
    {6325,"Dissonance Field",237546,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Empress creates a dissonance field which disrupts the sound associated with magic. The dissonance field absorbs nearby magical effects until it runs out of resonance. Once its resonance depletes, the field erupts in a Sonic Discharge.\n\n\n\nPlayers casting magical effects inside the dissonance field also deplete it of resonance.",-1,6326,0,0,743,6337,2,6336,0},
    {6326,"Sonic Discharge",237546,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Sonic Discharge inflicts $123504s1 Physical damage to all players.",-1,0,0,0,743,6666,3,6325,0},
    {6327,"Call Water",135862,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Wise Mari summons a Corrupt Living Water from one of the four smaller fountains to attack the players.",-1,5616,0,32,672,0,5,5612,0},
    {6328,"Whirling Blade",236303,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Wind Lord Mel'jarak hurls his blade at a random player's location, inflicting $121898s1 Physical damage to all players in the blade's path. After the blade reaches its destination, it returns to Wind Lord Mel'jarak. The blade also inflicts $121898s1 Physical damage to all players in its return path.",-1,0,0,0,741,6329,1,0,0},
    {6329,"Rain of Blades",615303,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Wind Lord Mel'jarak rains blades down on all players, inflicting $122407s1 Physical damage every $122406t1 seconds for $122406d.",-1,0,0,0,741,6697,2,0,0},
    {6331,"Recklessness",132352,2,0,2,{"wago"},"When Wind Lord Mel'jarak sees a group of his warriors fall in battle, he becomes reckless for the remainder of the fight. This increases his damage dealt by $122354s1% and damage taken by $122354s2%. This effect stacks.",19,0,0,0,741,6555,6,0,0},
    {6332,"Fate of the Swarm",537253,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Each group of Mel'jarak's swarm shares health with their fellow swarm members.",-1,0,0,0,741,6333,9,6299,0},
    {6333,"Impaling Spear",615361,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Up to four players can use the weapon racks left by the Mantid army to gain the Impaling Spear ability.\n\n\n\nImpaling Spear stuns a target for $122224d. Any damage dealt directly to the target by a player causes the target to break free.",-1,0,0,0,741,6300,10,6299,0},
    {6334,"Kor'thik Elite Blademaster",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,6335,43087,0,741,0,19,6299,0},
    {6335,"Kor'thik Strike",615302,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Kor'thik Elite Blademasters focus a single player and strike them in unison, each inflicting $123962s1 Physical damage.",-1,0,0,0,741,0,20,6334,0},
    {6336,"Stage One: A Perilous Battle!",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},nil,-1,6325,0,0,743,6340,1,0,0},
    {6337,"Eyes of the Empress",133016,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Empress gazes deeply into the eyes of her current target, inflicting the target with the Eyes of the Empress effect. This effect stacks up to $123707s1 times. The Empress charms and transforms a player into a Servant of the Empress if the effect reaches maximum stacks.",-1,6544,0,1,743,6338,5,6336,0},
    {6338,"Dread Screech",252188,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Grand Empress Shek'zeer lets loose a Dread Screech at two random players, inflicting $123743s1 Physical damage to each player and their nearby allies within $123743A1 yards.$[4,6,7\n\n\n\nIn 25 Player raids, Shek'zeer looses a Dread Screech at five random players.$]",-1,0,0,0,743,6339,7,6336,0},
    {6339,"Cry of Terror",136131,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Empress incites terror on a random player, causing them to inflict $123792s1 Shadow damage to players every $123788t1 sec.",-1,0,0,0,743,0,8,6336,0},
    {6340,"Stage Two: The Empress Retreats!",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},"When the Empress runs out of sha energy, she retreats to her chrysalis and calls for her royal guard. Once she is fully recharged, or all of the Set'thik Windblades are defeated, the empress will emerge from her chamber.",-1,6545,0,0,743,6341,9,0,0},
